---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Grievance officer — book·lore"
  description="Mandatory contact under India's IT Rules 2021."
>
  <section class="spine page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">book·lore</a> / <a href="/legal/">colophon</a> / grievance officer</p>
      <h1>Grievance officer</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>
        Per the <strong>Information Technology (Intermediary Guidelines and Digital Media
        Ethics Code) Rules, 2021</strong>, the following contact handles complaints related
        to book-lore.oriz.in.
      </p>

      <div class="card">
        <p><strong>Name:</strong> Chirag Singhal</p>
        <p><strong>Designation:</strong> Grievance Officer</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a></p>
        <p><strong>Address:</strong> Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India 751001</p>
        <p><strong>Response time:</strong> Acknowledgement within 24 hours; resolution within 15 days.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What you can report</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Entries that you believe infringe your copyright.</li>
        <li>Specific quoted material that exceeds fair use — name the URL and quote so we can act quickly.</li>
        <li>Content that violates the IT Rules (defamation, obscenity, threats, impersonation).</li>
        <li>Privacy concerns under the DPDP Act 2023 — access, correction, deletion of your data.</li>
        <li>Account takeover or security incidents.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Please include: a clear description of the issue, the URL(s) involved, proof you
        are the rights-holder (for copyright), and your contact details.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .card {
    margin-block: 1.25rem 1.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .card p { margin: 0.375rem 0; }
</style>
